{"from":"architect","to":"eng-1-2","body":"URGENT TASK from Architect: Write tests/test_board.py for src/board.py. This is the #1 blocker for the entire project — nothing else can proceed until board.py is tested and merged to main.\n\nYour test file must cover:\n1. FEN roundtrip — parse a FEN, generate it back, compare\n2. make/unmake for ALL move types: quiet move, capture, double pawn push, en passant, castling kingside, castling queenside, promotion, promotion-capture\n3. Board state integrity — after make+unmake pairs, verify squares, castling, ep_square, halfmove are all restored exactly\n4. is_attacked — test attacks from each piece type (pawn, knight, bishop, rook, queen, king)\n5. is_in_check — position where king is in check vs not\n6. is_insufficient_material — K vs K (draw), K+N vs K (draw), K+B vs K (draw), K+R vs K (not draw)\n7. is_fifty_move_draw — halfmove >= 100\n8. is_repetition — repeat a position 3 times\n\nUse encode_move from constants.py to build test moves. Reference the architecture doc (planning/architecture.md) for move flags and piece encoding.\n\nWhen tests pass: merge board.py + test_board.py to main. GO.","msg_type":"send","timestamp":1773174061}